OnTrack supports multiple build methods to suit different workflows and target platforms.

## Build Methods at a Glance

| Method | Best For | Reproducible | Cross-Platform |
|--------|----------|-------------|----------------|
| **Nix flake** | NixOS users, CI, reproducible builds | Yes | Yes (4 platforms) |
| **Cargo** | Rust developers | No | Via cross-rs |
| **pip/maturin** | Python developers | No | Host only |
| **PyInstaller** | Distributing desktop binaries | No | Host only |
| **buildozer** | Android APK | No | Android only |
| **Build scripts** | One-command builds | No | Yes |

## Quick Reference

```bash
# Nix — build everything
nix build .#ontrack-rs-cli
nix build .#ontrack-rs-gui
nix build .#ontrack-py

# Nix — run checks
nix flake check

# Nix — enter dev shell
nix develop          # combined
nix develop .#python # python only
nix develop .#rust   # rust only

# Scripts — build everything
./scripts/build-all.sh --all

# Scripts — cross-compile Rust
./scripts/cross-compile-rs.sh --target aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu

# Scripts — build Python
./scripts/build-python.sh --all
```

## Output Directory

All build scripts output to `dist/` at the repository root:

```
dist/
├── rust/
│   └── host/
│       ├── ontrack          # CLI binary
│       └── ontrack-gui      # GUI binary
├── python/
│   ├── wheel/               # Python wheel
│   ├── standalone/          # PyInstaller binary
│   └── android/             # APK file
├── x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/
│   ├── ontrack
│   └── ontrack-gui
├── aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu/
│   └── ontrack
└── nix/
    ├── ontrack-rs-cli/
    ├── ontrack-rs-gui/
    └── ontrack-py/
```

